This paper deals with image analysis and proposes a framework for ensemble sparse models. The paper discusses the use of these models in image restoration and unsupervised clustering, which are both subfields of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of boosted approaches, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Theoretical analysis of the ensemble model involves information theory (cs.IT) and the experiments involve compressed sensing (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, and cs.MM.
